{"title": "Katherine Clark\u2019s guest for Trump speech is immigration advocate - The Boston Globe", "url": "https://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2017/02/28/katherine-clark-guest-for-trump-speech-immigration-advocate/hkhxkN8CvLIsXC4L1VYwFN/story.html", "text": "Congresswoman Katherine Clark will bring Veronica Serrato, an immigration advocate and daughter of Mexican immigrants, as her guest to Tuesday night\u2019s address by President Trump, her office said.\n\nAmid controversy over the president\u2019s recent moves to deport more illegal immigrants, ban travel from majority-Muslim countries and block refugees, Clark is one of several politicians to invite immigrants to the talk, Trump\u2019s first to Congress.\n\nAdvertisement\n\n\u201cI want Trump to know that he\u2019s not just addressing Congress; he\u2019s addressing families at home who are hurt by his divisive policies,\u201d Clark said in a statement.\n\nClark, a Democrat whose district includes suburbs to the north and west of Boston, was one of many federal lawmakers who boycotted Trump\u2019s inauguration in January.\n\nGet Fast Forward in your inbox: Forget yesterday's news. Get what you need today in this early-morning email. Sign Up Thank you for signing up! Sign up for more newsletters here\n\nSerrato is founding executive director of Project Citizenship, an organization that provides free services to legal permanent residents to help them become naturalized citizens. She is also one of five children of naturalized Mexican immigrants, according to Clark\u2019s office.\n\nSerrato said her organization received an unprecedented number of calls since Trump\u2019s inauguration and again after the administration put in place a travel ban on immigrants from seven majority-Muslim countries.\n\n\u201cMany of our clients are frightened and anxious about the plans of the new administration,\u201d Serrato said in a statement provided by Clark\u2019s office.\n\nAdvertisement\n\nSerrato is an attorney who has also worked at the Volunteers Lawyers Project and the Wilmer Hale Legal Services Center of Harvard Law School, according to Clark\u2019s office.\n\n\u201cCitizenship is the only security and protection from deportation or exclusion,\u201d Serrato said in the statement.", "source": "BostonGlobe.com", "publish_date": "2017-02-28", "type": "article"}